OZ Tenpin Bowling
Fun On The Lanes!

Located just 10 minutes from the CBD, our centre was established in 1979 and is Ballarat’s best entertainment for the WHOLE family! Whether your 4 or 104 our centre is equipped for you to enjoy a game of tenpin bowling. We have light weight bowling balls, bowling ramps, bumper bowling and wheel chair access meaning everyone can enjoy a game! Our centre offers 16 synthetic lanes, great assortment of arcade games and full café! Everything you need in one place for a great family outing. We pride ourselves on old fashion friendly customer service and look forward to seeing you very soon! For a full price list, please contact us!

Monday – Sunday

Located just a stone’s throw away from Chrinside Park shopping centre. Our centre offers 28 lanes of tenpin bowling with an 8 lane private area perfect for your next work or group function. With a fully licensed café offering a great selection of ready to eat snacks, meal deals, coffees and drinks.  Once your finished bowling we have pool tables, jukeboxes and you can even earn tickets through our great selection of arcade games to earn prizes every time you visit!
For our more serious bowlers we even have a fully stocked pro-shop offering on-the-spot orders along with bookings for ball drilling and ball resurfacing.

Nestled behind Epping YMCA on Miller Street in Epping and surrounded by ample parking spaces, Oz Tenpin Epping offers 26 lanes of tenpin bowling, including an 8 lane private corporate area, perfect for work and group functions where each and every lane features automatic bumpers and computerized scoring!

A fully licensed café with a great selection of ready to eat snacks including kids meal deals, coffees and drinks.  There’s a great selection of redemption arcade games along with disco glow bowling and a coin operated jukebox filled with all the latest hits that will bring a smile to every bowlers face!
For the league bowlers, we have a fully stocked pro shop offering on-the-spot orders and bookings for ball drillings!

Spare is a story about a tenpin bowler who is practicing by himself in a bowling alley. The film is based on the painting Wheat Field, with Cypresses, which was made by Vincent van Gogh. The feeling of agitation in the painting come in part from the mass of twisting lines, dynamic curves and colours repeated several times throughout, and this characteristic is what inspired the choice of professional bowling as an activity.
